                  <handDesc>
                     
                     <handNote xml:id="h1" script="Ethiopic">
                        <seg type="script"/>
                        <seg type="ink">Black, red</seg>
                        Scribe: Gabra Mikāʾel. Gabra Mikāʾel
                        is mentioned as the scribe in the supplication on <locus target="#91rb">91rb</locus>.<date>19th century (?)</date>
                        <list type="abbreviations">
                           <item>
                              <abbr>ይ፡ ሕ(ዝ)፡</abbr> for <expan>ይበሉ፡ ሕዝብ፡ </expan> (e.g., <locus target="#29rb">29rb</locus>, 29va)</item>
                           <item>
                              <abbr>ይ፡ ካ፡</abbr> for <expan>ይበል፡ ካሕን፡ </expan> (e.g., <locus target="#29rb">29rb</locus>, 29va, 31va)</item>
                           <item>
                              <abbr>ይ፡ ዲ፡</abbr> for <expan>ይበል፡ ዲያቆን፡ </expan> (e.g., <locus target="#29va">29va</locus>, 31va)</item>
                           <item>
                              <abbr>ፍቱ፡</abbr> for <expan>ፍትሕተ፡ ወንጽሕተ፡ ረስያ፡ ለዛቲ፡ ነፍስ፡ </expan>
                              (e.g., <locus target="#36ra">36ra</locus>b)</item>
                           <item>
                              <abbr>ፍቱ፡ / ፍቱ፡ ወን(ጹሐ)፡ ረ(ስ)፡ ለዝ፡ በድ</abbr> for <expan>ፍቱሐ፡ ወንጹሐ፡ ረስዮ፡
                                 ለዝንቱ፡ በድን፡ </expan> (e.g., <locus target="#41va">41va</locus>b,
                              42rab)</item>
                        </list>
                        <seg type="rubrication">Nomina sacra; name of the scribe; a few lines on the
                           incipit page, alternating with black lines; incipit of each section of
                           the text; names of Hebrew letters in Ps. 118 (e.g., fols. 34vab, 36vab,
                           37ra); some other words: e.g., halle luya (e.g., fols. 5vab, 6rab, 6vab,
                           7rab), ṣällǝyu (e.g., fols. 29ra, 35va, 37va), kǝśtat (e.g., fols. 32vb,
                           51ra), qǝdmä wängel (e.g., fols. 35ra, 37ra), wa-kāʿǝba (e.g., fols.
                           35va, 37rb), dǝḫrä wängel (e.g., fols. 47ra, 52va), wa-ʾǝmzǝ (e.,g.,
                           fols. 121vab, 122rb), täśahalänni (e.g., fol. 123rb); abbreviations;
                           elements of Ethiopic numerals; elements of the punctuation signs and text
                           dividers.</seg>
                     </handNote>
                  </handDesc>
                  <decoDesc>

                     <decoNote type="frame" xml:id="d1">
                        <locus target="#5r">5r</locus> (incipit page of the Text): uncoloured
                        ornamental frame; interlaces, anthropomorphic motifs (eyes).</decoNote>
                  </decoDesc>
                  <additions>
                     <list>
                        <item xml:id="e1">
                           <desc type="findingAid">- Coloured threads have been inserted in the upper
                              corner/outer margins of fols. 29, 68, 91, 97, 99. - Notes written in
                              the main hand in frames in the upper margin referring to the content
                              of the Ms.: fols. 41r, 56v, 60r, 62r, 66r; sometimes written in recent
                              crude blue ballpoint pen: e.g., fols. 48r, 51v.</desc>
                        </item>
                        <item xml:id="e3">
                           <desc>- <locus target="#137v">Fol.  137v</locus>: Crude drawing of a human on a horse holding a spear (perhaps St. George slaying the dragon). - Erasures marked with thin lines: fols. 11ra, 59vb, 110vb. - Corrections written over erasures: fols. 45ra, 50ra, 129ra. - Immediate corrections marked by dashes above and below the words: <locus target="#110va">fol.  110va</locus>. - Omitted letters or words inserted interlineally: e.g., fols. 10rb, 11vb, 14rb, 20rb, 26va. - The scribe used compressed script: e.g., fols. 51ra-51vb, 55va-56ra, 57rb-57vb. - The word እገሌ(ት) is marked above and below by a series of dashes: e.g., fols. 68rb, 68vab, 76vab, 77va, 78rab. - Spaces for rubricated names of the donors left unfilled: e.g., fols. 12rb, 20rb, 20vab, 21rab, 28rab. - Scribbles and doodles: e.g., fols. 1r, 1v, 10v, 12v, 19r, 39r.</desc>
                        </item>
                     </list>
                  </additions>
